50 lessons I learned after seven years in crypto  1. Comparing yourself against others is a recipe for failure.   2. Hard mode is when everyone is bullish.  3. CT is an illusion. Most people aren't nearly as well off as people think.  4. Money won't make your life any more fulfilling than it already is.   5. There are so many ways to improve your chances to make it other than trading.   6. Position sizing and risk management are the most important skills to outsized gains.   7. The mindset that will net you insane profits is the same one that could lead to being broke.   8. Optimism is one of the biggest growth hacks.   9. Knowing the right person is worth its weight in gold.   10. Trading in a nutshell is understanding what has and what hasn't been priced in.  11. Buying what's in demand at higher prices is better than buying trash cheaper.   12. Look for opportunity now rather than dwelling on the past.   13. Never borrow conviction from others   14. Don't be so eager to short strength.   15. Play to your strengths or you will be weak at everything.  16. Uncertainty is part of the game. Embrace it.   17. Volatility means opportunity. Don't fear it.   18. The best opportunities are in extremes not the middle.   19. Journaling is better than most paid groups out there.    20. Alts that outperform do so for a reason. Don't just fade that kind of signal.   21. If you can't explain the value proposition in under half a minute it's probably too complicated.   22. Price moves not based on the product but the vision in many cases.  23. People on CT are more willing to help than you think. Put yourself out there.   24. Most people are too conservative on bottoms and too aggressive on tops.   25. Most profit will be made off a few positions. Make your runners count.   26. Don't take out winners to put into losers. It rarely works.   27. Making outsized gains requires you to actually take risk.   28. There is such a thing as too much information. Simple is best.   29. It is easier to make it with other smart people than by yourself.  30. In many cases it's better off to take the alpha over the beta play.   31. Be open to experimenting with new things.   32. It's EV+ to be open minded about new things instead of being skeptical about everything.  33. It costs nothing to be kind to others and the payoff can be great.   34. Writing and networking are two of the most EV+ plus actions you can do that costs little.   35. Leverage is a tool like everything else. People just choose to use it the wrong way and get rekt.   36. Mistakes today are an investment for tomorrow if you are willing to learn from it.   37. There is no bull or bear market. The market just is.   38. The best tech doesn't always win.   39. Sometimes story matters more than product.   40. Never measure your net worth based on your portfolio peak.   41. Before buying the dip ask yourself why is this asset being priced here.   42. Be opinionated and don't be afraid to be wrong.   43. There is no magic setup that will make you money. Everything depends on context.   44. Trading is not about being right. It's about setting probabilities and payoffs to be in your favor.   45. Losing streaks are an inevitability statistically. Just try not to lose too much when you are in a slump.   46. Don't feel pressured to make it over an arbitrary timeframe. It will just make you perform worse.   47. Patience is such a big edge that few people take advantage of.   48. Market PTSD is a very real thing you need to learn how to shrug off.   49. Don't just think about nominal returns but also risk adjusted returns.   50. You can be right and still lose money because of bad execution.